			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey everyone, I was wondering what strategy you guys use during solos, chain-casting, or give pet items and heal him?  I've always used items n heals, but now that I'm reaching my mid 50's and such, it's getting much harder to keep up with heals.  I've attempted to chain-cast multiple times, but have yet to be truly successful.  Root always breaks after reclaim energy, but I think this is because I was pulling with Burst of Flame and not with Malosi (makes root last for full duration).  Is that correct?
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">How I Chain-Cast (plz tell me if I'm doing anything wrong)</span>
<br />

<br />
Welll...
<br />
I summon pet, BO5 & DS him, send him in to fight, stand close enough to hear the "TARGET sinks into the ground" message.  Watch pets hp, when he gets low, I wait for "TARGET sinks into the gound" message, and immediatley reclaim energy (with my shovel of ponz/torch of Alna).  I then resummon my pet while mob is rooted.  and repeat.  
<br />

<br />
BUT many times root fails while I'm in the middle of summoning.  Is my "not using Malosi" the reason for this?
<br />

<br />
<span style="text-decoration: underline">Also's...</span>
<br />

<br />
Also...I use my twisted ring to shorten the summoning time (8.5 seconds, normally 10 seconds) but I was wondering if I should try and find a summoning haste III.  Is it better?  Do they stack?  Is a Summoning Haste III item impossible for me to come by for too little of a change?
<br />

<br />
Also...If I have a summoning efficiency (makes summoning pets use less mana, right?)  will reclaim energy, reclaim 75% (not sure about the number) of the <span style="font-weight: bold">original</span> mana cost, or the mana cost after the focus effect?
<br />

<br />
Also...What items do you guys have to help you chain-cast?
<br />

<br />
Also...Do you guys have any tips that I could use to help me become more successful?
<br />

<br />
Also...After you reclaim energy, do you immediatley summon, or run a lil ways away?
<br />

<br />
Thanks alot guys, I really wanna learn how to do this.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin" border="0" /> 
