			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Seems you might need to go back to the tried and true old method before reclaiming gave you back 75% of mana spent summoning pet. As long as you are medding between pets, on horse or otherwise, you should lose no mana at all. An enshrouded veil (SE3) will help out alot. 
<br />

<br />
This is highly mob dependent, but here's the gist of it:
<br />

<br />
1. Summon pet, BO, DS, pull or send pet in.
<br />
2. Med while pet is fighting.
<br />
3. When pet is at 20% health, start summoning a new pet.
<br />
4. As soon as you start summoning new pet, type /pet get lost (but do not hit enter)
<br />
5. Wait until your cast bar is about a half a sec to 1 sec from finishing, then hit enter.
<br />

<br />
Effect, 1 dead low health pet, a new one in it's place a half a sec later.
<br />

<br />
6. BO and DS
<br />
7. Rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
Requires a bit of practice to get the timing right, but that's how it was done old school. No worries about reclaiming pet, and having root break mid cast etc.
<br />

<br />
I chained 17 pets on Tarbul Earthstrider when I was lvl 52 without ever losing a lick of mana.  Bring lots of malachite. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=394587"> Sillaen 67th Arch Convoker</a><br>Cazic Thule.
<br />
