			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, couple of things...
<br />

<br />
Pulling with a malaise spell only helps the root spell land. I doubt it has an impact on duration. I may be wrong.
<br />

<br />
Reclaim energy (as it is currently) gives you back 75% of the mana spent when casting pet. 
<br />

<br />
Between lv51 and 64, healing pets become very hard because you only have access to lower-level healing spells that have a long cast time, and a long recast time, and high mana cost. The plus side is that your lv51+ Earth pets become deadly effective for chaining.
<br />

<br />
Enshrouded Veil is something you will come to cherish if you take the pet-chaining road. Highly recommended. It's about the only item that can help you there.
<br />

<br />
Method described by Sillaen is the best one to use. Forget reclaim while in battle. Use it if the pet is low on HP after mob is dead. Reclaim, resummon a fresh pet. Otherwise, do what he described, it's perfect.
<br />

<br />
Always carry lots of malachite. At lv51, I started carrying 2-4 stacks at all time. It's cheap, so no reason ever to be left without any. No pet = dead mage.
<br />

<br />
Sillaen's method is furthermore effective that 61+ pets enrage when low on HP. This allows you to almost wait for enrage to start before starting to summon a new pet. Practice it now, and you will love it lv61+.
<br />

<br />
Purchase or make (pottery I think) a White ceramic band. This way you wont have to mem Burst of flame. Always do at least 1pt of damage to the mob to get full XP. Do quest for Clay bracelet while you're at it. Invaluable tools that will last even at lv65 and 500AAs.
<br />

<br />
A very very good place to practice chaining is the Dulak Harbor boats camp. Try to get the Stormwave, as it is the lower level, and has the fewest spawns (7 I think). Pirates are far apart, so it's next to imposible to have multiple pulls. Good gem drops and cash, and the captain has nice rare loot for casters. The hard part is reaching Dulak before lv54 (when you get Veil of Elements). SoW potions recommended for the Guntak tunnel run.
<br />

<br />
Pfff... more than I intended. Hope it helps *wink*<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.legion-whiterose.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"> <img src="http://img21.photobucket.com/albums/v63/Loralor/loralorEpic.jpg" border="0" /> </a>
