	<tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><span class="name"><a name="176339"></a><b>Jochan Galadar</b></span><br /><span class="postdetails">The Gospel According to St. Jochan<br /><img src="images/gallery/Mortal Kombat/Mortal_Kombat_-_Reiko.gif" alt="" border="0" /><br /><br />Joined: 23 Jul 2001<br />Posts: 749<br />Location: Upstate NY, USA</span><br /></td>
		<td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=176339&amp;sid=984fabfedf077f7c9e0ec8b3f0d85563#176339"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu May 13, 2004 7:50 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
			        <td valign="top" align="right" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="ignore.php?mode=add&amp;username=Jochan Galadar&amp;topic=14227&amp;sid=984fabfedf077f7c9e0ec8b3f0d85563"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_ignore.gif" alt="Add User to Ignore List" title="Add User to Ignore List" border="0" /></a> <a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=176339&amp;sid=984fabfedf077f7c9e0ec8b3f0d85563"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">summon pet, BO5 & DS him, send him in to fight, stand close enough to hear the "TARGET sinks into the ground" message. Watch pets hp, when he gets low, I wait for "TARGET sinks into the gound" message, and immediatley reclaim energy (with my shovel of ponz/torch of Alna). I then resummon my pet while mob is rooted. and repeat. 
<br />

<br />
BUT many times root fails while I'm in the middle of summoning. Is my "not using Malosi" the reason for this? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Also...I use my twisted ring to shorten the summoning time (8.5 seconds, normally 10 seconds) but I was wondering if I should try and find a summoning haste III. Is it better? Do they stack? Is a Summoning Haste III item impossible for me to come by for too little of a change</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Every bit of spell haste you can get (up to the 50% cap) will benefit you, period. The two Summoning Haste III items I am aware of are the Kobold Jester Crown (1-2k, sometimes less) and the Brell's Girdle (4-6k).  The only real drawback to the Jester Crown is the large INT penalty.  OTOH if you are reclaim chaining, you are not consuming much mana, if any.  I used a KJC until I maxed Quick Summoning.  In a pinch, you can go to your local home city and throw some trinkets at your Tribute Master and get the Tribute buff version.  Also, Summoning Haste III does not stack with any other spell haste foci, but if you can get a Blessing of Reverence buff from a cleric, that will cut down your cast times further.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Also...If I have a summoning efficiency (makes summoning pets use less mana, right?) will reclaim energy, reclaim 75% (not sure about the number) of the original mana cost, or the mana cost after the focus effect? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
It gives you 75% of the actual mana used to summon the pet, after all efficiency bonuses.  In other words, the more efficient your summons are, the less mana you get back reclaiming your pet.  The net result is very very slightly more efficient reclaim chaining, but hardly noticeable.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Also...What items do you guys have to help you chain-cast? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
These days, nothing.  I use a Torch of Alna.  I used to have an Enshrouded Veil and a KJC.  For AA's, I chose Run Speed 3, Regen 3, Spell Casting Mastery 3, Quick Summoning 3, Improved reclaim, and Elemental Pact.  I added Pet Discipline later.  First Aid 3 is also worth considering.
<br />

<br />
Items that boost your hit points, ac, and possibly agility will help for when root breaks early.  AA's that help this include Combat Agility, Combat Stability, and Channeling Focus, along with STA and possibly AGI.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Pulling with a malaise spell only helps the root spell land. I doubt it has an impact on duration. I may be wrong. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I can't say I am 100% certain, but I believe the way root spells work is the mob gets several chances to save during the root's duration.  Having debuffed a mob's magic resist should help assure full duration.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Also...After you reclaim energy, do you immediatley summon, or run a lil ways away? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I immediately summon.  If you are more comfortable at a distance, that's okay.
<br />

<br />

<br />
This is the best I advice I can give you:  If you are casting your debuff (Malxx) and are still getting regular root breaks, you are probably soloing mobs that are significantly higher level than your pet, or perhaps around the same level as your pet.  There are two solutions to this predicament.  First is to pull slightly lower level mobs. Second is to duo with a distractor partner, someone to pull aggro from you while you resummon.  This could be a simple arrangement like another mag as a partner, but really it could be any class.
<br />

<br />
Good luck, and keep practicing.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
