				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Yenkins_Babblefoot wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Also...After you reclaim energy, do you immediatley summon, or run a lil ways away?
<br />
-Yenkins Babblefoot-
<br />
Mage of the 52nd Element
<br />
Stromm</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
By using just distance, you can use the reclaim/chainnig with the air pet.  It takes a big area free from adds, a good judge of distance, and balls of steel to continue the summons with a mob bearing down on you, but it can be done.  Even with the earth pet and its root, I recommend getting some distance before you reclaim to give you a little leeway if the root breaks early.  
<br />

<br />
If you are reclaim/chaining, I highly recommend a summoning haste III item.  It is much better to have the Kobold Jester's Crown even with it's big neg int hit.  Reclaim/chaining is not mana intensive, but very time senestive.  
<br />

<br />
The pet chaining using the /pet get lost commad just before the summons finishes is much easier to get down.  In ethier case, pratice the technique with a green mob unitl you can keep it rooted forever.  
<br />

<br />
Good luck.  Once you have it mastered, you will have the ablity to keep most mobs busy forever.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
