				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">[quote="Jochan Galadar"]</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Pulling with a malaise spell only helps the root spell land. I doubt it has an impact on duration. I may be wrong. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I can't say I am 100% certain, but I believe the way root spells work is the mob gets several chances to save during the root's duration.  Having debuffed a mob's magic resist should help assure full duration.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Anytime the mob takes damage, it gets another save vs the root.  That includes melee hits from your pet.  Having an instant reclaim item that you click immediately upon seeing the "'Target' sinks into the group message" reduces the number of times you pet melee attacks your mob after the root takes effect and reduces the number of saves made which makes it more likely to hold while summoning a new pet.  The Malxx line of spells will help everytime the pet makes a save vs root.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
